11 (i) The name, address, and taxpayer identification number of
12 the owner and each qualified taxpayer that has been allocated a
13 portion of the annual credit awarded on the eligibility statement
14 for that year.
15 (ii) The amount of the annual credit allocated to each
16 qualified taxpayer identified under subparagraph (i) for that year
17 and the applicable tax against which the credit will be claimed.
18 (iii) The total of the amounts listed for each qualified
19 taxpayer under subparagraph (ii), demonstrating that the total does
20 not exceed the amount listed on the eligibility statement for that
21 year.
22 (b) Notify the department of treasury of any changes to the
23 information reported under subdivision (a)(ii) in the time and
24 manner as prescribed by the department of treasury.
25 (9) As used in this section:
26 (a) "Adjusted annual federal credit amount" means 1/6 of the
27 aggregate amount of federal credit awarded to a qualified project
28 over its federal credit period.
29 (b) "Allocation report" means the annual report required to be
KAS H05885'25 (H-1) sog07q

21
1 submitted to the department of treasury under subsection (8).
2 (c) "Applicable tax" means a tax imposed under the income tax
3 act of 1967, 1967 PA 281, MCL 206.1 to 206.847, or under section
4 476a of the insurance code of 1956, 1956 PA 218, MCL 500.476a.
5 (d) "Application window" means the first quarter, January 1
6 through March 31, or the third quarter, July 1 through September
7 30, of the award cycle. If either the first or last day of the
8 application window falls on a nonbusiness day, then the starting or
9 ending date is the next business day.
10 (e) "Award" means a binding reservation letter of eligibility
11 issued by the authority for a housing opportunity tax credit
12 attributable to a qualified project during an award cycle, setting
13 forth the amount of the housing opportunity tax credit to be
14 claimed in each year of the credit period.
15 (f) "Award cycle" means each calendar year over which the
16 authority approves and allocates housing opportunity tax credits
17 for qualified projects.
18 (g) "Award cycle cap" means the sum of the following:
19 (i) The base annual amount as determined under subsection (4)
20 for each calendar year of the credit period.
21 (ii) The amount, if any, by which the award cycle cap
22 prescribed under this section for the preceding award cycle exceeds
23 the total of all housing opportunity tax credits awarded by the
24 authority in that award cycle.
25 (iii) The amount of housing opportunity credits recaptured or
26 otherwise disallowed under subsection (7) in the preceding calendar
27 year or otherwise returned to the authority since the prior award
28 cycle.
29 (h) "Credit period" means the period of 6 calendar years
KAS H05885'25 (H-1) sog07q

22
1 beginning with the calendar year in which a building that is part
2 of a qualified project is placed in service. If a qualified project
3 consists of more than 1 building, then the owner may elect to
4 either treat all buildings as 1 project and begin the credit period
5 when the last building is placed in service or treat each
6 building's credit period independently on a building-by-building
7 basis.
8 (i) "Designated reporter" means the owner of the qualified
9 project or the person designated by the owner under subsection (6).
10 (j) "Eligibility statement" means a statement issued by the
11 authority to the owner of a qualified project certifying that the
12 project is a qualified project and specifying the amount of the
13 housing opportunity tax credit that may be claimed each year of the
14 credit period, the years that comprise the credit period, the name,
15 address, and taxpayer identification number of the owner, the date
16 of issuance, and any additional information prescribed by the
17 authority.
18 (k) "Federal credit period" means the 10-year period described
19 under section 42(f)(1) of the internal revenue code, 26 USC 42.
20 (l) "Federal low-income housing tax credit" or "federal credit"
21 means the credit allowed under section 42 of the internal revenue
22 code, 26 USC 42.
23 (m) "4% qualified project" means a qualified project that is
24 eligible for both of the following:
25 (i) A federal low-income housing tax credit under section
26 42(h)(4) of the internal revenue code, 26 USC 42.
27 (ii) A bond issued under section 44c for which the authority is
28 not the bondholder with respect to the bond proceeds.
29 (n) "Flow-through entity" means an entity that for the
KAS H05885'25 (H-1) sog07q

23
1 applicable tax year is treated as a subchapter S corporation under
2 section 1362(a) of the internal revenue code, 26 USC 1362, a
3 general partnership, a trust, a limited partnership, a limited
4 liability partnership, or a limited liability company, and that for
5 the tax year is not taxed as a corporation for federal income tax
6 purposes. Flow-through entity does not include any entity treated
7 as a corporation under section 699 of the income tax act of 1967,
8 1967 PA 281, MCL 206.699.
9 (o) "Housing opportunity tax credit" means a tax credit
10 authorized to be claimed against an applicable tax under section
11 279, 679, or 821 of the income tax act of 1967, 1967 PA 281, MCL
12 206.279, 206.679, and 206.821, or section 476a of the insurance
13 code of 1956, 1956 PA 218, MCL 500.476a, whichever is applicable.
14 (p) "Internal revenue code" means the United States internal
15 revenue code of 1986.
16 (q) "Member", when used in reference to a flow-through entity,
17 means a shareholder of a subchapter S corporation, a partner in a
18 general partnership, a limited partnership, or a limited liability
19 partnership, a member of a limited liability company, or a
20 beneficiary of a trust that is a flow-through entity, as long as
21 the shareholder, partner, member, or beneficiary, as applicable, is
22 considered a shareholder, partner, member, or beneficiary under
23 applicable state law governing such flow-through entity.
24 (r) "New construction" means newly constructed housing units
25 and does not include the rehabilitation or acquisition of existing
26 buildings or adaptive reuse projects. New construction includes the
27 demolition necessary for the construction of new housing units.
28 (s) "Owner" means a person holding a fee simple interest in a
29 qualified project or a leasehold interest pursuant to a ground
KAS H05885'25 (H-1) sog07q

24
1 lease in the land on which a qualified project is located.
2 (t) "Person" means an individual, bank, financial institution,
